@NODE "Vorwort" "Preface"

    100 MByte and a bit quieter.

    After years of waiting, the  development  of  the  floppydisk  has
    finally done a definite step forward. The hopeless try of pressing
    2.88 MB of data onto one of the beloved and hated  magnetic  disks
    had  failed  and now iomega presented a hopefully successor to the
    market. With a tough media with 100 MB of space and  speed,  which
    is  a  multiple  of  a normal floppydrive, and additional features
    like passwordprotection and powersaving, the drive convinced in  a
    complete way.

    Unfortunately iomega once more  like  most  other  firms  had  not
    thought  about  the  existence  of other platforms than WinPCs and
    Macs. The software bought together with the drive can directly  be
    put  into  the  trashcan (Attention: specialwaste!). Luckily there
    are some Amiga-enthusiasts who are compiling  tools  so  that  the
    Amiga-user can use the special features of the drive.

    A contribution  to  this  is  the  Z100-package,  which  currently
    insists only in one application, but it had to be start somewhere.
    By the way I can check up the interests  regarding  this  kind  of
    software. You should know:

                     No feedback --> No development

    In this sense I hope that I don't put my spare time into the  sand
    and  that  it  will  show to me, that the shareware-concept is the
    right way.

                                        Thomas Omilian, September 1997

    P.S.: Also it may sound selfish to you: This programm is dedicated
    to  myself,  because  I'm strictly convinced on the concept of the
    drive and I'm very satisfied with it.

@ENDNODE
