@NODE "MegaGiro" "Mega/Giro"

    Mega/Giro - The Money-Account-Manager

    This software is only available in german.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "Knack" "Knack"

    Knack - The GUI for DMS,LhA,PGP and more

    Knack helps users to archive  complete  disks  without  typing  in
    those  confusing shell-commands. More it is an utility to decrunch
    archives those you get from  internet  and  other  sources.  These
    files are packed mostly with LHA/DMS oder other archivers.
    But to decrunch files from  the  archives  you  must  learn  about
    parameters and functions of the needed decruncher.
    With Knack it is possible to manage crunching and  decrunching  of
    files only by using the mouse-driven interface.

    Knack uses MUI (MagicUserInterface) developed by Stefan Stuntz, so
    the user can easily change the design.
    The integrated online-help makes it easy  to  get  information  on
    every window and gadgetfunction.

    The archivers LhA, LZX, DMS and MUI  are  not  supplied  with  the
    distribution.  You should be able to get it from most local bbs or
    from an aminet-mirror.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "MegaNote" LINK "Mega/Note"

    Mega/Note - Cute little notepad

    Mega/Note (MNote) is a cute, little  notepad  with  99  pages.  On
    every  page is place for 6 rows with 24 columns. All settings such
    as window/cursor-positon could be automatically saved on exit,  so
    they  will  be  restored on next startup. It is possible to export
    data to printer/clipboard and  import  them  from  clipboard.
    The program is written in  pure  assembler.  Font-sensitivity  and
    localisation  (WB  2.1)  is  implemented. MNote requires Kickstart
    2.04.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "MegaBLZ" LINK "Mega/BLZ"

    Mega/BLZ - Fast Access to german Bank-IDs

    This software is only available in german due to it's meaning.  If
    there  are  some  people who need a localized version I may change
    this.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "MegaFish" "Mega/Fish"

    Mega/Fish - The Public-Domain-Manager

    is a complete replacement for the Tool Aquarium. (Aquarium manages
    the  contents  of  the Free Distributable Library compiled by Fred
    Fish.) Mega/Fish is able to manage more than one  library  !  With
    it's  help  it  is  possible  to  find any program existing on the
    installed libraries. You are able to browse through the  libraries
    just  for  checking  out  what  treasures  were  sleeping in those
    libraries.

@ENDNODE

